===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*peh₃-}}
The {{glossary|adjective}} is derived from Late {{inh|en|enm|potable|t=drinkable, potable}},<ref>{{R:MED Online|entry=pō̆tāble|pos=adj|id=MED34166}}</ref> from {{der|en|frm|-}}, {{der|en|fro|potable}} (modern {{cog|fr|potable|t=drinkable, potable}}), and from its {{glossary|etymon}} {{der|en|LL.|pōtābilis|t=drinkable, potable}}, from {{der|en|la|pōtāre|t=to drink}} + {{m|la|-bilis|pos=suffix forming adjectives indicating a capacity or worth of being acted upon}}.<ref name="OED">{{R:OED Online|pos=adj.'' and ''n|id=148734|date=December 2006|nodot=1}}; {{R:Lexico|pos=adj}}</ref> ''Pōtāre'' is the {{glossary|present}} {{glossary|active}} {{glossary|infinitive}} of {{m|la|pōtō|t=to drink}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*peh₃-|t=to drink}}. The English word is cognate with {{cog|ca|potable}}, {{cog|it|potabile}}, {{cog|es|potable}}.<ref name="OED"/>

The {{glossary|noun}} is derived from the adjective.

